org.kynosarges.tektosyne.subdivision

Class AddEdgeResult

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.kynosarges.tektosyne.subdivision.AddEdgeResult

  • public final class AddEdgeResult
extends java.lang.Object
    Contains the result of adding an edge to a Subdivision. Immutable class containing the result of the Subdivision.addEdge(org.kynosarges.tektosyne.geometry.PointD, org.kynosarges.tektosyne.geometry.PointD) method of the Subdivision class.

    • Field Detail

      • addedEdge

        public final SubdivisionEdge addedEdge
        One of the two added SubdivisionEdge instances, if any. Set to a valid instance if Subdivision.addEdge(org.kynosarges.tektosyne.geometry.PointD, org.kynosarges.tektosyne.geometry.PointD) succeeded, else to null. A valid SubdivisionEdge is directed from the specified start to end coordinates.

      • addedFaceKey

        public final int addedFaceKey
        The SubdivisionFace.key() of the added SubdivisionFace, if any. Set to a non-negative value if Subdivision.addEdge(org.kynosarges.tektosyne.geometry.PointD, org.kynosarges.tektosyne.geometry.PointD) succeeded and a SubdivisionFace was added along with addedEdge, else to a negative value.

      • changedFaceKey

        public final int changedFaceKey
        The SubdivisionFace.key() of the changed SubdivisionFace, if any. Set to a non-negative value if Subdivision.addEdge(org.kynosarges.tektosyne.geometry.PointD, org.kynosarges.tektosyne.geometry.PointD) succeeded, else to a negative value.

    • Method Detail

      • isEdgeAdded

        public boolean isEdgeAdded()
        Indicates whether an edge was added to the Subdivision.
        Returns:
        true if changedFaceKey is equal to or greater than zero, else false.
